*FULL BRIGHTNESS PLEASE*
.
Well, I have been planning to get a peek of this - once in a 6800years - phenomenon but sadly it's been so cloudy in Bangalore for the last days. 
.
Plus the light pollution here would make this a next to impossible feat. 
.
But thanks to @_.saumya_ I have been able to get the most realistic glimpse of the comet and therefore I am posting the same here. ☄️
.
Here is a small spec sheet I found about Neowise Comet-
Perihelion on 3rd July, 5km width,  64km/sec, mostly water, 6788-year orbital period. FASCINATING!
.
.
.
